<subSubSection id="079E653C5345FF8BFEF380D6FE0DF8D5" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4F3B36B75345FF8BFEF380D6FD0DF90D" blockId="27.[151,1436,1384,1915]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis id="7DF0EAA55345FF8BFEF380D6FE9CFA41" bold="true" box="[199,308,1493,1519]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Remarks</emphasis>
. This species is easily recognised by the large oval tentacle scales (two on basal segments), the multiple (4–8) oral papillae, the pentagonal oral shield that is bordered distally by a fringe of small papillae, and the rod-shaped disc spines that can be terminated by small thorns (
<figureCitation id="D7BF2A325345FF8BFDBD831FFC77F999" box="[905,991,1564,1591]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1894]" captionTargetId="figure-26@18.[151,1436,181,1894]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 6. (A) Ophiacantha veterna, MNHN IE.2009.1562, dorsal outline. (B) MNHN IE.2009.1563, ventral view. (C–E) Ophiosabine cuspidata, MNHN IE.2009.1558, C: dorsal outline, D: dorsal view, E: ventral view. (F) Ophiotreta spectabilis, MNHN IE.2009.1564, dorsal view. (G–H) Ophiolimna bairdi, MNHN IE.2009.1571, G: dorsal and H: ventral views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404692" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404692/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Fig. 6F</figureCitation>
). This species has been identified as an associate (
<bibRefCitation id="2B154B465345FF8BFF398342FE4FF9F5" author="O'Hara, T. D. &amp; Rowden, A. A. &amp; Williams, A." box="[269,487,1600,1627]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" pagination="925 - 934" refId="ref35027" refString="O'Hara, T. D., Rowden, A. A. &amp; Williams, A. (2008) Cold-water coral habitats on seamounts: do they have a specialist fauna? Diversity and Distributions, 14, 925 - 934. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1472 - 4642.2008.00495. x" type="journal article" year="2008">
O’Hara 
<emphasis id="7DF0EAA55345FF8BFF5F8342FE0DF9F4" box="[363,421,1600,1626]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">et al.</emphasis>
2008
</bibRefCitation>
) of the colonial deep-water coral 
<taxonomicName id="88844D345345FF8BFD5E8343FBC7F9F4" authorityName="Duncan" authorityYear="1873" box="[874,1135,1600,1626]" class="Anthozoa" family="Caryophylliidae" genus="Solenosmilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scleractinia" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="variabilis">
<emphasis id="7DF0EAA55345FF8BFD5E8343FBC7F9F4" box="[874,1135,1600,1626]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Solenosmilia variabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Both MD50 samples that contained 
<taxonomicName id="88844D345345FF8BFF3E8366FE0BF9D0" authorityName="Sars" authorityYear="1872" box="[266,419,1636,1663]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiacanthidae" genus="Ophiacantha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiacanthida" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="spectabilis">
<emphasis id="7DF0EAA55345FF8BFF3E8366FE0BF9D0" box="[266,419,1636,1663]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">O. spectabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(to 
<quantity id="887C9B525345FF8BFFFA8367FD8BF9D1" box="[462,547,1636,1663]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" unit="mm" value="8.5">8.5 mm</quantity>
dd) also contained 
<taxonomicName id="88844D345345FF8BFCCE8366FC28F9D0" authorityName="Duncan" authorityYear="1873" box="[762,896,1636,1663]" class="Anthozoa" family="Caryophylliidae" genus="Solenosmilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scleractinia" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="variabilis">
<emphasis id="7DF0EAA55345FF8BFCCE8366FC28F9D0" box="[762,896,1636,1663]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">S. variabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see MNHN online collections database, https:// science.mnhn.fr/institution/mnhn/item/search).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4F3B36B75345FF8BFEF383AFFE0DF8D5" blockId="27.[151,1436,1384,1915]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
Phylogenetic evidence shows conclusively that this species belongs in the family 
<taxonomicName id="88844D345345FF8BFA4383AFFABFF968" authorityName="Paterson" authorityYear="1985" box="[1143,1303,1708,1734]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiotomidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiacanthida" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="family">Ophiotomidae</taxonomicName>
rather than the 
<taxonomicName id="88844D345345FF8BFEF583D3FDF7F945" authority="(O'Hara et al. 2017)" baseAuthorityName="O'Hara" baseAuthorityYear="2017" box="[193,607,1744,1771]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiacanthidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiacanthida" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="family">
Ophiacanthidae (
<bibRefCitation id="2B154B465345FF8BFF4B83D2FDFFF945" author="O'Hara, T. D. &amp; Hugall, A. F. &amp; Thuy, B. &amp; Stohr, S. &amp; Martynov, A. V." box="[383,599,1744,1771]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" pagination="415 - 430" refId="ref34885" refString="O'Hara, T. D., Hugall, A. F., Thuy, B., Stohr, S. &amp; Martynov, A. V. (2017) Restructuring higher taxonomy using broad-scale phylogenomics: the living Ophiuroidea. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution, 107, 415 - 430. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ympev. 2016.12.006" type="journal article" year="2017">
O’Hara 
<emphasis id="7DF0EAA55345FF8BFFE883D2FDBDF944" box="[476,533,1744,1770]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">et al.</emphasis>
2017
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, and consequently it is transferred here to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="88844D345345FF8BFA9983D3FA8FF944" authorityName="Verrill" authorityYear="1899" box="[1197,1319,1744,1770]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiotomidae" genus="Ophiotreta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiacanthida" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7DF0EAA55345FF8BFA9983D3FA8FF944" box="[1197,1319,1744,1770]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Ophiotreta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
pending a revision of this family. Many of the existing ophiotomid genera appear to be non-monophyletic. In the phylogeny, it is sister to a clade that includes the tropical Indo-Pacific species 
<taxonomicName id="88844D345345FF8BFD83821BFAC0F89D" authority="(Koehler, 1904)" baseAuthorityName="Koehler" baseAuthorityYear="1904" box="[951,1384,1816,1843]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiotomidae" genus="Ophiopristis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiacanthida" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="procera">
<emphasis id="7DF0EAA55345FF8BFD83821BFB0FF89C" box="[951,1191,1816,1842]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Ophiopristis procera</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="2B154B465345FF8BFA8D821BFAC8F89D" author="Koehler, R." box="[1209,1376,1816,1843]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" pagination="1 - 176" refId="ref32152" refString="Koehler, R. (1904) Ophiures de mer profonde. Siboga-Expeditie, 45, 1 - 176 pls. 1 - 36." type="journal article" year="1904">Koehler, 1904</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="88844D345345FF8BFEA3823FFD90F8F9" authority="(Koehler, 1904)" baseAuthorityName="Koehler" baseAuthorityYear="1904" box="[151,568,1852,1879]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiotomidae" genus="Ophiopristis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiacanthida" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="luctosa">
<emphasis id="7DF0EAA55345FF8BFEA3823FFED4F8F8" box="[151,380,1852,1878]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Ophiopristis luctosa</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="2B154B465345FF8BFFB8823FFD87F8F9" author="Koehler, R." box="[396,559,1852,1879]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" pagination="1 - 176" refId="ref32152" refString="Koehler, R. (1904) Ophiures de mer profonde. Siboga-Expeditie, 45, 1 - 176 pls. 1 - 36." type="journal article" year="1904">Koehler, 1904</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
which also have a fringe of papillae on the dorsal margin of the oral shields (
<bibRefCitation id="2B154B465345FF8BFEAB8262FE31F8D5" author="O'Hara, T. D. &amp; Stohr, S." box="[159,409,1888,1915]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" pagination="33 - 141" refId="ref35165" refString="O'Hara, T. D. &amp; Stohr, S. (2006) Deep water Ophiuroidea (Echinodermata) of New Caledonia: Ophiacanthidae and Hemieuryalidae. Tropical Deep-Sea Benthos, 24, 33 - 141." type="journal article" year="2006">O’Hara &amp; Stöhr 2006</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
